Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs` to hook platform-native callbacks directly:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity =>
        {
            // App losing focus (partially visible)
        })
        .OnStop(activity =>
        {
            // App fully backgrounded
        }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app =>
        {
            // App entered background
        }));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**

- **Cross-platform alternative:** If you don't need platform-specific APIs, use `Window.Stopped` instead — it maps to `OnStop` on Android and `DidEnterBackground` on iOS automatically.
- **Keep handlers fast** — Android enforces ~5s ANR timeout; iOS has limited background time.
- **`OnPause` ≠ `OnStop`** — `OnPause` fires when the app loses focus (notification shade, split-screen) but may still be visible. `OnStop` fires when fully hidden.

**Cross-platform equivalent (simpler):**

```csharp
protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
{
    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);
    window.Stopped += (s, e) =>
    {
        // Fires on both Android (OnStop) and iOS (DidEnterBackground)
    };
    return window;
}
```
